SPARK // Visual Language Spec  
“Live Circuit” – Anti-Vibe / Hacker Console / Industrial Sci-Fi  
-------------------------------------------------------------

1.  Palette Tokens (Tailwind)
   --void: #050505;            // bg-void
   --matrix: #00FF41;           // text-matrix / border-matrix / shadow-matrix
   --alert: #FF3030;            // text-alert / border-alert / shadow-alert
   --process: #FFD400;          // text-process / border-process / shadow-process
   --scanline: rgba(0,255,65,.08);

2.  Base Layer (global.css)
   @theme {
     --font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
     --color-void: #050505;
     --color-matrix: #00FF41;
     --color-alert: #FF3030;
     --color-process: #FFD400;
   }

   body {
     background: var(--color-void);
     color: var(--color-matrix);
     font-family: var(--font-mono);
     font-size: 13px;              /* high-density */
     line-height: 1.3;
     text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;
     image-rendering: pixelated;
   }

3.  CRT Shell (overlay)
   <div class="fixed inset-0 pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
     <div class="crt-scanlines"></div>
   </div>

   .crt-scanlines::before {
     content: "";
     position: absolute;
     inset: 0;
     background: repeating-linear-gradient(
       0deg,
       transparent,
       transparent 2px,
       var(--scanline) 2px,
       var(--scanline) 3px
     );
     animation: scan 8s linear infinite;
   }

   @keyframes scan {
     0%   { transform: translateY(0); }
     100% { transform: translateY(6px); }
   }

4.  Wire Primitive (SVG inside React component)
   <svg class="w-full h-full">
     <path
       id={wireId}
       strokeWidth="2"
       fill="none"
       class={cn(
         "wire",
         status === "success" && "wire-success",
         status === "failure" && "wire-failure",
         status === "processing" && "wire-processing"
       )}
     />
   </svg>

   /* Base wire */
   .wire {
     stroke: rgba(0,255,65,.35);
     filter: drop-shadow(0 0 2px var(--matrix));
     transition: stroke .3s ease;
   }

   /* States */
   .wire-success   { stroke: var(--matrix); }
   .wire-failure     { stroke: var(--alert); animation: flash .4s infinite; }
   .wire-processing  { stroke: var(--process); }

   @keyframes flash {
     0%,100% { opacity: 1; }
     50%     { opacity: .2; }
   }

5.  Nervous-Pulse (Framer Motion)
   const pathRef = useRef<SVGPathElement>(null);
   const length = useMemo(() => (pathRef.current?.getTotalLength() ?? 0), [pathRef]);

   const pulseVariants = {
     idle:    { pathLength: 0, opacity: 0 },
     success: { pathLength: 1, opacity: 1, transition: { duration: .6, ease: "easeOut" } },
     failure: { pathLength: .4, opacity: 1, transition: { duration: .2 } },
     processing: {
       pathLength: [0,1],
       opacity: [0,1,1,0],
       transition: { duration: 1.2, repeat: Infinity, ease: "linear" }
     }
   };

   <motion.path
     ref={pathRef}
     d={pathData}
     strokeWidth="3"
     strokeLinecap="round"
     fill="none"
     initial="idle"
     animate={status}
     variants={pulseVariants}
     style={{ strokeDasharray: length, strokeDashoffset: length }}
   />

6.  Text & Cursor
   .text-glow { text-shadow: 0 0 4px var(--matrix); }
   .cursor { display: inline-block; width: 10px; height: 18px; background: var(--matrix); animation: blink 1s infinite; }

   @keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }

7.  Utility Classes (Tailwind)
   .bg-void      { background-color: var(--color-void); }
   .text-matrix  { color: var(--color-matrix); }
   .text-alert   { color: var(--color-alert); }
   .border-matrix { border-color: var(--color-matrix); box-shadow: 0 0 4px var(--color-matrix); }
   .border-alert  { border-color: var(--color-alert); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--color-alert); }

8.  Usage Example
   <div className="bg-void text-matrix font-mono p-4">
     <div className="text-glow">init nervous_system…</div>
     <LiveCircuitWire status={status} />
     <span className="cursor" />
   </div>

Drop these classes/states into any React component; swap the status prop to watch the schematic come alive.

